KUNLE Afolayan has made a giant leap to get budding and established filmmakers in Nollywood on the global stage. The film director recently inked a partnership deal with Netflix and the University of Southern California to train budding and established filmmakers and intending in the art of post-production. Afolayan recently announced the partnership while urging intending filmmakers yearning to get a certificate course in Cinematic art to come on board.   Rita Dominic: Secrets of my 23 years acting career     Glo Battle of the Year Nigeria goes on air next week     Bimbo Manuel features Monalisa Chinda, Francis Duru in…   Read Also: Bimbo Manuel features Monalisa Chinda, Francis Duru in stage play, Philomena “The School of Cinematic Arts (SCA) at the University of Southern California (USC) and Netflix have partnered for a series of training workshops in Africa. The first in the series of talent development initiatives is a post-production training programme in collaboration with Kunle Afolayan Productions (KAP) Film and Television Academy. - Advertisement - “Get a joint certificate from Kunle Afolayan Production academy and University of Southern California School of Cinematic Art. Netflix and USC School of Cinematic Arts in conjunction with KAP academy have introduced Film & TV Industry Training in Africa. KAP Film and Television Academy will host post-production workshops in Nigeria.”